Quick update on scoring and rewards 🧵

We’ve seen some good questions about how QRTs, replies, and original posts are scored — and how we’re evolving the system.

1️⃣ Early approach
At first the subnet worked quite differently, we only counted QRTs and replies from verified accounts. This helped test whether interaction from credible users could serve as a proxy for engagement quality. It wasn’t perfect, but it gave us a solid calibration baseline.

2️⃣ How it evolved
Once we built a stronger list of verified Bittensor accounts, we added original posts into scoring. Both posts and QRTs now contribute. Weighting depends on how many verified Bittensor followers an account has — keeping influence network-based, not inflated by raw follower counts.

3️⃣ What’s next
We’re exploring whether to increase the relative weight of original posts compared to QRTs. This won’t overhaul the system overnight, but we’ll adjust based on data and community input.

Curious to hear what the community thinks, would that improve fairness?

4️⃣ On fairness and exposure
Some have asked whether paying for QRTs “games” the system. We understand the concern. The subnet currently values reach and engagement from influential, Sybil-resistant accounts - regardless of how that interaction happens.

That said, we’re reviewing these dynamics and investigating what we can do to make sure they reflect genuine influence, not manipulation. Expect ongoing fine-tuning to keep things balanced and fair.

Our goal remains simple:
🧠 Reward genuine insight and real reach from real participants — not noise.

Thanks for the feedback. We’ll keep refining openly and will likely have some updates ready for next Tuesday.

🧩 Update on QRT Scoring and Quality System

Hi everyone 👋

After reviewing recent feedback and the imbalance caused by QRT scoring, we’re making an adjustment to ensure rewards better reflect genuine contributions.

🚫 QRT Scoring Disabled

Starting tomorrow (after validator updates), QRTs will no longer receive scores.
From now on, only original posts will contribute to your miner score and rewards.
This change will make emissions more balanced and aligned with quality content creation.

🧠 Fixing Non-Deterministic Scoring

Our current scoring LLM occasionally produces different outputs for the same post because of its reasoning variability.
Longer posts are especially affected — the more tokens generated, the less stable the score.

We’re transitioning to a deterministic LLM for scoring and validation to ensure every post is evaluated consistently.

🌟 Introducing Quality Check

To promote thoughtful, factual contributions, we’re adding a Quality Check layer.
Posts that pass this filter will receive a score multiplier (×1.2 or ×1.5) depending on their evaluation.
This helps reward not just activity, but real substance.

⚖️ Weight Adjustment

We’re also updating how account weights are calculated:

followers^1.5  →  followers^1.2


This reduces the advantage of very large accounts and gives smaller miners a fairer chance to compete on quality.

💪 What This Means

These updates aim to create:

Fairer emissions distribution

Higher-value, organic reach

A stronger link between quality and visibility

To earn stronger scores:

Focus on creating original, high-quality posts

Engage authentically and build genuine followers within the community

Nuance is about rewarding signal, not noise — and these refinements move us closer to that goal.
